      "weather": "FINE",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Wide open. ACTIVE DUTY (1) is in great form, winning the Colac Cup two back for the former stable and running very well back to 1400m at first try here. Extra trip suits and should be tough to catch. MATRON SAMSING (6) is the emerging galloper in red-hot form, winning three of her last five. Lifted to score this class and course and distance last time and will go close again. OUR COUVER (3) placed here fresh and will strip fitter for it. Back in grade and out in trip both pluses. VENTING (4) was fourth fresh and is also fitter for the extra ground. One of the leading chances. VALIMI (2) is a former NSW galloper having first try in this area and will give a sight. Was an all the way Eagle Farm winner last year returning a rating that has a fair bit on these save for ACTIVE DUTY's Colac Cup win so keep very safe.",
